Fig. 2. –

Schismatoclada spathulata
D. Strid & Razafim. 
A.
Dissected

corolla tube of a brevistylous flower showing the indumentum and the insertion of the stamens inside the tube; 
B.
Brevistylous flower (corolla removed) showing pedicel, unequal calyx lobes, ovary, and style and stigma; 
C.
Dissected corolla tube of a longistylous flower showing the indumentum and the insertion of the stamens inside the tube; 
D.
A brevistylous flower showing a pedicel, unequal calyx lobes, an ovary, and a style and stigma; 
E.
Young, beaked fruit with persistent calyx lobes; 
F.
Broadly winged seed with irregular margins. [
